      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STELLINA (1) has been solid in finishing fifth at her last two appearances at Newcastle, the latest from this barrier. Should enjoy an economical run and finds what looks to be a winnable assignment. THE EX HORSEIST (8) has been racing at Menangle of late and there was merit in the latest effort when he came from a wide draw for fourth, beaten 7 metres. If things go his way from the second line he could measure up to these. PETES BIG JIM (2) didn't do a bad job when sixth from the back row here last time out and looks well served by this barrier. TIL HEAVENS ROCKN NZ (5) continued the consistent form when fourth from the back row last start. Go well.",
